[block=center id=about][size=18]About[/size][/block]\

Luckboard is a no fluff league. Coaches are players here. Teams are sets here. Players are stones here.

The aim of luckboard is to move the game of orcs and lizardmen towards the seriosness of classic boardgames such as chess and go by removing the fluff completely and by providing a balanced environment which still lets enough space for players to compile their game sets with much freedom and to react on the builds of their opponents. Design and the term stone were in fact taken from go. Stones are get neutral names and the result is somewhat weakly refer man in his environment. American Football position names are too detailed to apply to stones with general stats. Anyway, stone names are not important in luckboard. I hope that people who were only warded off by the fantasy fluff will give luckboard a try.

A player can have a single dedicated set at a time. That set consists of base stones and special stones. Players have the same base stones but their special ones may differ. There are two kinds of special stones: extra and premium stones. Extra stones are introduced sometimes and everybody gets them. Premium stones are introduced on various events and will be added as a reward and thus will be not available for everyone.

Each player has fourteen base stones and can take one or two additional special stones to each game. The player can allocate 9 normal and 5 double skills to the base stones per game and a stone may have games + 2 skills maximum. More info in the [url=#bbcode_tournamentformat]Tournament Format[/url] section. Special stones have their fixed skills which can not be changed.

For each game the player gets three Re-rolls and 100k gold for inducements which can be used to buy regular inducements or – more importantly – one or two special stones.

Only a single tournament is held at a time. Once it is done then the application period – usually a week or two – of the next tournament will be officially announced along with its format, deadline and other information. Players have to apply to each tournament separately like for the official FUMBBL tournaments. There is no obligation in participation or activity. More about the tournament format below.

Stone sets are not progressing and the base set could be assembled in a common way only. Team options has to be filled up completely to get accepted into a tournament. The required amount of skills to get allocated depends of the expected maximum number of matches (skills = 14 × M) of the upcoming tournament. Creating a set is fast but allocating the skills is usually not. Once in a draw, it is worth to note the skills of the next opponent and decide about the special stones to be taken to the game.


