[block=center id=mod][size=18]FFB Client Mod[/size][/block]\

Luckboard has its own FFB client mod. For best user experience it is advised to play and spectate Luckboard games with that instead of the standard FFB client. Get it [url=https://github.com/FUMBBLPlus/luckboard/releases/tag/mod]HERE[/url]. Currently it works on Windows only but it is planned to support Linux and OSX as well soon.

Changes implemented:
[ulist]\
[li][url=/i/517291]Wooden board[/url].
[li]Bloodspots removed.
[li]Most of the sounds got customized. The rest are replaced with silence. Currenty only /boo, /clap, and /laugh are supported.
[/ulist]\
Changes planned:

[list=1]\
[li]Custom ball.
[li]Custom prone and stun markers.
[li]More custom sounds.
[li]Custom dice.
[li]Customise the rest of the UI.
[/list]\


[block=center id=technical][size=18]Technical[/size][/block]\

The [url=/p/race?id=1230]roster[/url] has each stone explicitely set with its own icon and zero cost. Re-Roll cost is 1 gold in the [url=/p/ruleset?id=518]ruleset[/url] and the roster starts with three golds which can be used only for that puropse: to buy three Re-Rolls. Ruleset requires 14 players minimum for a team so each stones has to get taken.

Technically, special stones are star players in a [url=/p/race?id=1228]separate roster[/url]. A new roster gets cloned for each player which lets us to manage the player's individual special stones. Cloning is done with Python scripts which I refused to publish by Christer. The prices of special stones will be one of 25k, 50k, 75k, and 100k. The highest priced are designed to disallow a second special stone to get taken to the game.

Modding is done by downloading FFB client JAR files, deleting hash check files thus removing validation, adding/replacing resources (images/sounds), editing config (INI) files. This is done by prepare.bat. To start the client, the proper java command has to get issued which is done by luckboard.bat. The exe file is a mere launcher of luckboard.bat. It looks nicer in the Open With context menu with the Luckboard icon.

